<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 2:28PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central Madison
and northeastern Beaverhead Counties through 245 PM MDT...
At 228 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northeast of Dillon, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Sheridan, Alder and Laurin.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for
southwestern Montana.</instruction>
